    <note>Lou(2) Zhao [8094] Quan(2) Bangyan's [165] menren. XNYL, 104.12b, 184.17a. According to Yuan(1) Xie's funerary inscription for Lou(2) Yue [3624] (WJ, 11.1a), the Lou(2) were originally one lineage (yizu) and that Zhao was a descendant of the branch that remained in Wuzhou and Yue a descendant of the branch that moved to Mingzhou. I am, therefore, identifying Zhao's great grandfather, Ying [19944], as the lineage nephew of Yu's [3623] grandfather, Hao [19943]. The Wuzhou Lou are identified as jia 'a' and the Mingzhou root lineage, as branch 'b.' CBD, 5, 3722-3.</note>
